minor.comment: Create a new instance function called `getVerboseOutput` on `StringBufferTerminalProvider` and mark `getVerbose` as deprecated.

patch.comment: Include CHANGELOG.md in published releases again
Improve the PrintUtilities API to handle an edge case when word-wrapping a final line
Include missing `type` modifiers on type-only exports.

minor.comment: Eliminate a const enum from the public API.

Change the `eolCharacter` property value of `StringBufferTerminalProvider` to `\n` from `[n]`. This does not change the default `getOutput()` result, but removes the `[n]` characters from the `getOutput({ normalizeSpecialCharacters: false })` result.
Allow use of 'preventAutoclose' flag in StdioSummarizer.
Replace the `colors` dependency with `supports-color` for detecting if STDOUT and STDERR support color.

patch.comment: Fix a recent regression causing `Error: Cannot find module 'colors/safe'` (GitHub #4525)

minor.comment: Introduce a Terminal, Colors, AsciEscape, and some related APIs. These APIs were previously in the @rushstack/node-core-library package. See https://github.com/microsoft/rushstack/pull/3176 for details.

patch.comment: Fix broken link to API documentation
Fix line endings in published package.

Fix an issue where `PrintUtilities.printMessageInBox` would throw if the message contains a word that is longer than the box width. In this case, `printMessageInBox` will print bars above and below the message, and then print the message lines, allowing the console to wrap them.
Update type-only imports to include the type modifier.

minor.comment: Add support for a custom line prefix in `PrintUtilities.wrapWords`.
Add a `PrintUtilities.wrapWordsToLines` function that is functionally identical to `PrintUtilities.wrapWords`, except that it returns an array of lines instead of a joined string with line breaks.

patch.comment: Fix a minor logic issue for TextRewriterTransform cleanup
Change the peer dependency selector on `@types/node` to a wildcard (`*`).

minor.comment: Move the @types/node dependency to an optional peerDependency.

patch.comment: The wrapWords method now respects existing spaces and newlines in a pre-formatted message.
Update the package.json repository field to include the directory property.

minor.comment: Use ITerminal instead of Terminal to allow for compatibility with other versions of @rushstack/node-core-library.

patch.comment: Upgrade the `@types/node` dependency to version to version 12.

minor.comment: Export console printing utilities from the PrintUtility class.
